{"title_page": "2001 Russian Indoor Athletics Championships", "text_new": "{{Infobox Athletics Championships\n |Name = 2001 Russian Indoor Athletics Championships\n |Logo = \n |Optional caption = \n |Size = \n |Host city = [[Moscow]]\n |Athletes participating = \n |Events = 28\n |Dates = 16\u201318 February\n |Stadium = [[Alexander Gomelsky Universal Sports Hall CSKA]]\n |Stadium image = [[File:CSKA Universal Sports Hall Moscow.jpg|250px]]\n |Previous = [[1998 Russian Indoor Athletics Championships|1998]]\n |Next = [[2000 Russian Indoor Athletics Championships|2000]]\n}}\nThe '''2001 [[Russian Indoor Athletics Championships]]''' ({{lang-ru|\u0427\u0435\u043c\u043f\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0442 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u043b\u0451\u0433\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0430\u0442\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u0432 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 2001}}) was the 10th edition of the national championship in indoor [[track and field]] for [[Russia]]. It was held on 16\u201318 February at the [[Alexander Gomelsky Universal Sports Hall CSKA]] in [[Moscow]]. A total of 28 events (14 for men and 14 for women) were contested over the three-day competition.<ref>[http://www.gbrathletics.com/nc/rusi.htm Russian Indoor Championships]. GBR Athletics. Retrieved 2019-08-09.</ref> It was used for selection of the Russian team for the [[2001 IAAF World Indoor Championships]].\n\nThree individual championship records were set at the competition: [[Lyudmila Galkina]] won the women's long jump in {{T&Fcalc|7.00}},<ref>{{cite news |author=\u041b\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0425\u043e\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0430 |title=\u041b\u0451\u0433\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0430\u0442\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430. \u0417\u0438\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0447\u0435\u043c\u043f\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0442 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 |url=http://www.sport-express.ru/newspaper/2001-02-17/1_2/ |newspaper=[[Sport Express]] |date=2001-02-17 |accessdate=2014-10-09 |archiveurl=http://www.peeep.us/19383517 |archivedate=2014-10-09}}</ref> [[Tatyana Lebedeva]] won the women's [[triple jump]] in {{T&Fcalc|15.00}}, and [[Olga Kotlyarova]] set a time of 50.72 seconds to win the women's [[400 metres]].<ref>{{cite web | author = Sergey Tikhonov | title = Clean selection | url = http://lib.sportedu.ru/mirrors/www.iaaf-rdc.ru/t&f/2/18.htm | edition = Athletics | type = journal | year = 2001 | number = 3-4 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304074929/http://lib.sportedu.ru/mirrors/www.iaaf-rdc.ru/t%26f/2/18.htm | archivedate = 2016-03-04}}</ref>\n\nThe Russian Combined Events Indoor Championships was held separately on 16\u201318 February in [[Chelyabinsk]] at the [[Ural State University of Physical Culture]] arena. In the decathlon, fourth placer Nikolai Averyanov set a Russian under-23 record of 5571 points.<ref>{{cite news | author = Boris Titov | title = A new country record was set in Chelyabinsk | url = http://news.sport-express.ru/2001-02-21/8008/ | newspaper = [[Sport Express]]| date = 2001-02-21 | accessdate = 2014-10-09 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141013184337/http://news.sport-express.ru/2001-02-21/8008/ | archivedate = 2014-10-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0411\u043e\u0433\u0443\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 |title=\u0412 \u043c\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0436\u0435 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044f\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c \u043c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u0446\u044b |url=http://www.chelpress.ru/newspapers/ucourier/archive/20-02-2001/7/a70352.html |publisher=\u0423\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043a\u0443\u0440\u044c\u0435\u0440 |date=2001-02-20 |accessdate=2014-10-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912121421/http://www.chelpress.ru/newspapers/ucourier/archive/20-02-2001/7/a70352.html |archivedate=2014-09-12 }}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n\n===Men===\n{| {{MedalistTable|columns=2|type=Event}}