alifying standards, the Russian team for the [[2001 IAAF World Indoor Championships]] included:<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041b\u0451\u0433\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0430\u0442\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430. \u0421\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432 \u0441\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 |url=http://www.sport-express.ru/newspaper/2001-03-02/7_14/ |newspaper=[[Sport Express]] |date=2001-03-02 |accessdate=2014-10-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141013184432/http://www.sport-express.ru/newspaper/2001-03-02/7_14/ |archivedate=2014-10-13 }}</ref>\n\n===Men===\n\n*'''60 m:''' [[Sergey Bychkov]], [[Dmitri Vasilyev (runner)|Dmitriy Vasilev]]\n*'''200 m:''' [[Oleg Sergeyev (sprinter)|Oleg Sergeyev]]\n*'''400 m:''' [[Boris Gorban]], [[Andrey Semyonov (sprinter)|Andrey Semyonov]]\n*'''4 \u00d7 400 m relay:''' [[Boris Gorban]], [[Andrey Semyonov (sprinter)|Andrey Semyonov]], [[Ruslan Mashchenko]], [[Aleksandr Ladeyshchikov]], [[Dmitry Forshev]]\n*'''800 m:''' [[Yuriy Borzakovskiy]], [[Sergey Kozhevnikov]]\n*'''1500 m:''' [[Vyacheslav Shabunin]]\n*'''60 m hurdles:''' [[Evgeny Pechonkin]], [[Andrey Kislykh]]<sup>\u2021</sup>\n*'''High jump:''' [[Vyacheslav Voronin]], [[Yaroslav Rybakov]]\n*'''Pole vault:''' [[Pavel Gerasimov]]\n*'''Long jump:''' [[Evgeniy Tretjak]]<sup>\u2021</sup>, [[Vitaliy Shkurlatov]], [[Vladimir Malyavin]]\n*'''Triple jump:''' [[Igor Gavrilenko]]\n*'''Shot put:''' [[Pavel Chumachenko]]\n*'''Heptathlon:''' [[Lev Lobodin]]\n\n===Women===\n\n*'''60 m:''' [[Marina Kislova]], [[Larisa Kruglova]]\n*'''200 m:''' [[Anastasiya Kapachinskaya]], [[Natalya Mikhaylovskaya]]\n*'''400 m:''' [[Olga Kotlyarova]], [[Olesya Zykina]]\n*'''4 \u00d7 400 m relay:''' [[Olga Kotlyarova]], [[Olesya Zykina]], [[Yuliya Sotnikova]], [[Yuliya Pechonkina|Yuliya Nosova]], [[Natalya Khrushcheleva]], [[Natalya Antyukh]]\n*'''800 m:''' [[Yelena Afanasyeva]], [[Svetlana Cherkasova]]\n*'''1500 m:''' [[Natalya Gorelova]], [[Olga Kuznetsova]]<sup>\u2021</sup>\n*'''3000 m:''' [[Olga Yegorova]], [[Yelena Zadorozhnaya]]\n*'''60 m hurdles:''' [[Svetlana Laukhova]], [[Mariya Koroteyeva]]<sup>\u2021</sup>\n*'''High jump:''' [[Yuliya Lyakhova]], [[Yelena Gulyayeva]]\n*'''Pole vault:''' [[Svetlana Feofanova]], [[Yelena Isinbayeva]]\n*'''Long jump:''' [[Lyudmila Galkina]], [[Tatyana Kotova]]\n*'''Triple jump:''' [[Tatyana Lebedeva]], [[Oksana Rogova]]\n*'''Shot put:''' [[Larisa Peleshenko]], [[Svetlana Krivelyova]]\n*'''Pentathlon:''' [[Yelena Prokhorova]]<sup>\u2020</sup>, [[Natalya Roshchupkina]]<sup>\u2020</sup>\n\n<sup>\u2020</sup> Had exemption for selection and allowed not to compete at the national championships \n<sup>\u2021</sup> Later withdrew from the international competition\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n;Results\n*{{cite web | title = 2000. The best athletes of the world. Russian Indoor Championships Results - 2001 | url = http://lib.sportedu.ru/mirrors/www.iaaf-rdc.ru/t&f/1/101.htm | edition = Athletics | type = magazine | year = 2001 | number = 1\u20132 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180114021948/http://lib.sportedu.ru/mirrors/www.iaaf-rdc.ru/t%26f/1/101.htm | archivedate = 2018-01-14}}\n\n{{Russian Athletics Championships}}\n\n[[Category:Russian Indoor Athletics Championships]]\n[[Category:February 2001 sports events in Europe|Russian Indoor Athletics Championships]]\n[[Category:2001 in athletics (track and field)|Russian Indoor Athletics Championships]]\n[[Category:2001 in Russian sport|Russian Indoor Athletics Championships]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Moscow]]\n[[Category:2001 in Moscow]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Athletics Championships\n |Name = 2001 Russian Indoor Athletics Championships\n |Logo = \n |Optional caption = \n |Size = \n |Host city = [[Moscow]]\n |Athletes participating = \n |Events = 28\n |Dates = 16\u201318 February\n |Stadium = [[Alexander Gomelsky Universal Sports Hall CSKA]]\n |Stadium image = [[File:CSKA Universal Sports Hall Moscow.jpg|250px]]\n |Previous = [[1998 Russian Indoor Athletics Championships|1998]]\n |Next = [[2000 Russian Indoor Athletics Championships|2000]]\n}}\nThe '''2001 [[Russian Indoor Athletics Championships]]''' ({{lang-ru|\u0427\u0435\u043c\u043f\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0442 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u043b\u0451\u0433\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0430\u0442\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u0432 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 2001}}) was the 10th edition of the national championship in indoor [[track and field]] for [[Russia]]. It was held on 16\u201318 February at the [[Alexander Gomelsky Universal Sports Hall CSKA]] in [[Moscow]]. A total of 28 events (14 for men and 14 for women) were contested over the three-day competition.<ref>[http://www.gbrathletics.com/nc/rusi.htm Russian Indoor Championships]. GBR Athletics. Retrieved 2019-08-09.</ref> It was used for selection of the Russian team for the [[2001 IAAF World Indoor Championships]].\n\nThree individual championship records were set at the competition: [[Lyudmila Galkina]] won the women's long jump in {{T&Fcalc|7.00}},<ref>{{cite news |author=\u041b\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0425\u043e\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0430 |title=\u041b\u0451\u0433\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0430\u0442\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430. \u0417\u0438\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0447\u0435\u043c\u043f\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0442 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 |url=http://www.sport-express.ru/newspaper/2001-02-17/1_2/ |newspaper=[[Sport Express]] |date=2001-02-17 |accessdate=2014-10-09 |archiveurl=http://www.peeep.us/19383517 |archivedate=2014-10-09}}</ref> [[Tatyana Lebedeva]] won the women's [[triple jump]] in {{T&Fcalc|15.00}}, and [[Olga Kotlyarova]] set a time of 50.72 seconds to win the women's [[400 metres]].<ref>{{cite web | author = Sergey Tikhonov | title = Clean selection | url = http://lib.sportedu.ru/mirrors/www.iaaf-rdc.ru/t&f/2/18.htm | edition = Athletics | type = journal | year = 2001 | number = 3-4 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304074929/http://lib.sportedu.ru/mirrors/www.iaaf-rdc.ru/t%26f/2/18.htm | archivedate = 2016-03-04}}</ref>\n\nThe Russian Combined Events Indoor Championships was held separately on 16\u201318 February in [[Chelyabinsk]] at the [[Ural State University of Physical Culture]] arena. In the decathlon, fourth placer Nikolai Averyanov set a Russian under-23 record of 5571 points.<ref>{{cite news | author = Boris Titov | title = A new country record was set in Chelyabinsk | url = http://news.sport-express.ru/2001-02-21/8008/ | newspaper = [[Sport Express]]| date = 2001-02-21 | accessdate = 2014-10-09 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141013184337/http://news.sport-express.ru/2001-02-21/8008/ | archivedate = 2014-10-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0411\u043e\u0433\u0443\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 |title=\u0412 \u043c\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0436\u0435 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044f\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c \u043c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u0446\u044b |url=http://www.chelpress.ru/newspapers/ucourier/archive/20-02-2001/7/a70352.html |publisher=\u0423\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043a\u0443\u0440\u044c\u0435\u0440 |date=2001-02-20 |accessdate=2014-10-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912121421/http://www.chelpress.ru/newspapers/ucourier/archive/20-02-2001/7/a70352.html |archivedate=2014-09-12 }}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n\n===Men===\n{| {{MedalistTable|columns=2|type=Event}}\n|-\n|60 metres\n|[[Sergey Bychkov]]<br><small>[[Omsk Oblast]]</small>|| 6.68\n|[[Dmitri Vasilyev (runner)|Dmitriy Vasilev]]<br><small>[[Nizhny Novgorod Oblast]]</small>|| 6.70\n|[[Aleksandr Smirnov (sprinter)|Aleksandr Smirnov]]<br><small>[[Republic of Karelia|Karelia]]</small>|| 6.71\n|-\n|200 metres\n|[[Oleg Sergeyev (sprinter)|Oleg Sergeyev]]<br><small>[[Tyumen Oblast]]</small>|| 21.21\n|[[Sergey Bychkov]]<br><small>[[Omsk Oblast]]</small>|| 21.31\n|[[Sergey Blinov]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]/[[Nizhny Novgorod Oblast]]</small>|| 21.54\n|-\n|400 metres\n|[[Boris Gorban]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 46.33\n|[[Andrey Semyonov (sprinter)|Andrey Semyonov]]<br><small>[[Saint Petersburg]]/[[Sverdlovsk Oblast]]</small>|| 46.42\n|[[Ruslan Mashchenko]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]/[[Voronezh Oblast]]</small>|| 46.71\n|-\n|800 metres\n|[[Yuriy Borzakovskiy]]<br><small>[[Moscow Oblast]]</small>|| 1:49.95\n|[[Sergey Kozhevnikov]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]/[[Ryazan Oblast]]</small>|| 1:50.60\n|[[Boris Kaveshnikov]]<br><small>[[Sverdlovsk Oblast]]/[[Moscow Oblast]]</small>|| 1:51.67\n|-\n|1500 metres\n|[[Vyacheslav Shabunin]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 3:44.43\n|[[Roman Tarasov]]<br><small>[[Rostov Oblast]]</small>|| 3:48.52\n|[[Aleksandr Skvortsov (runner)|Aleksandr Skvortsov]]<br><small>[[Chuvashia]]</small>|| 3:48.64\n|-\n|3000 metres\n|[[Sergey Drygin]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 8:08.51\n|[[Rustam Yakupov]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 8:09.59\n|[[Evgeniy Konoyko]]<br><small>[[Sverdlovsk Oblast]]</small>|| 8:11.42\n|-\n|3000 m s'chase\n|[[Roman Usov (runner)|Roman Usov]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]/[[Kursk Oblast]]</small>|| 8:29.56\n|[[Andrey Olshanskiy]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]/[[Volgograd Oblast]]</small>|| 8:29.68\n|[[Pavel Potapovich]]<br><small>[[Kursk Oblast]]</small>|| 8:31.84\n|-\n|60 m hurdles\n|[[Evgeny Pechonkin]]<br><small>[[Novosibirsk Oblast]]</small>|| 7.66\n|[[Andrey Kislykh]]<br><small>[[Kemerovo Oblast]]</small>|| 7.88\n|[[Yuriy Volkov]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 7.90\n|-\n|High jump\n|[[Vyacheslav Voronin]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]/[[North Ossetia\u2013Alania]]</small>|| 2.30 m\n|[[Yaroslav Rybakov]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]/[[Yaroslavl Oblast]]</small>|| 2.28 m\n|[[Aleksey Kravtsov]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]/[[Stavropol Krai]]</small>|| 2.24 m\n|-\n|Pole vault\n|[[Pavel Gerasimov]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 5.70 m\n|[[Vasiliy Gorshkov]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 5.70 m\n|[[Pavel Burlachenko]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 5.65 m\n|-\n|Long jump\n|[[Evgeniy Tretyak]]<br><small>[[Krasnodar Krai]]</small>|| 8.11 m\n|[[Vladimir Malyavin]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 8.06 m\n|[[Vitaliy Shkurlatov]]<br><small>[[Volgograd Oblast]]/[[Bashkortostan]]</small>|| 8.05 m\n|-\n|Triple jump\n|[[Igor Gavrilenko]]<br><small>[[Krasnodar Krai]]</small>|| 17.00 m\n|[[Andrey Kurennoy]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]/[[Krasnodar Krai]]</small>|| 16.75 m\n|[[Igor Sautkin]]<br><small>[[Khabarovsk Krai]]</small>|| 16.64 m\n|-\n|Shot put\n|[[Pavel Chumachenko]]<br><small>[[Irkutsk Oblast]]</small>|| 20.91 m\n|[[Ivan Yushkov]]<br><small>[[Irkutsk Oblast]]/[[Novosibirsk Oblast]]</small>|| 19.11 m\n|[[Aleksandr Salnikov (shot putter)|Aleksandr Salnikov]]<br><small>[[Tatarstan]]</small>|| 18.78 m\n|-\n|4 \u00d7 200 m relay\n|[[Sverdlovsk Oblast]]<br>[[Vladimir Erykalov]]<br>[[Aleksandr Usov (sprinter)|Aleksandr Usov]]<br>[[Denis Sivov]]<br>[[Dmitry Forshev]]|| 1:26.44\n|[[Kaliningrad Oblast]]<br>[[Aleksandr Okhin]]<br>[[Anton Spiridonov]]<br>[[Aleksandr Sokolov (sprinter)|Aleksandr Sokolov]]<br>[[Dmitriy Pronin]]|| 1:26.84\n|[[Nizhny Novgorod Oblast]]<br>[[Dmitri Vasilyev (runner)|Dmitriy Vasilev]]<br>[[Aleksey Ofitserov]]<br>[[Dmitriy Buynov]]<br>[[Sergey Blinov]]|| 1:26.84\n|}\n\n===Women===\n{| {{MedalistTable|columns=2|type=Event}}\n|-\n|60 metres\n|[[Marina Kislova]]<br><small>[[Saint Petersburg]]</small>|| 7.19\n|[[Larisa Kruglova]]<br><small>[[Murmansk Oblast]]</small>|| 7.24\n|[[Natalya Mikhaylovskaya]]<br><small>[[Sverdlovsk Oblast]]</small>|| 7.28\n|-\n|200 metres\n|[[Anastasiya Kapachinskaya]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 23.24\n|[[Natalya Mikhaylovskaya]]<br><small>[[Sverdlovsk Oblast]]</small>|| 23.31\n|[[Oksana Ekk]]<br><small>[[Moscow]]</small>|| 23.37\n|-\n|400 metres\n|[[Olga Kotlyarova]]<br><small>[[Sverdlovsk Oblast]]</small>|| 50.72 {{AthAbbr|CR}}\n|[[Olesya Zykina]]<br><small>[[Tula Oblast]]</small>|| 51.33\n|[[Yuliya Sotnikova]]<br><small>[[Nizhny Novgorod Oblast]]</small>|| 52.